Forecasters say temperatures will remain in the hot category this week. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service says hot weather conditions are expected to continue until tomorrow in the province.While the heatwave is expected to come to an end today, forecasters say temperatures will remain in the hot category this week.Rainfall is expected over some parts with a chance of thundershowers. The temperatures will drop; they will move away a bit from the heatwave threshold temperatures but we are still going to be in the hot category, so in Gauteng and those northern provinces temperatures might still be in the thirties. (Edited by Neo Koza)